result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (8th) [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Concentration (>=.25)] and Operating w/ PAC (8th) [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Concentration (>=.25)]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (8th) [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Concentration (>=.25)] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (8th) [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Concentration (>=.25)] was dismissed by the court.

  • Carrie M. RACH was found guilty of OWI (8th) [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Concentration (>=.25)], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant in custody on WRIT.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, OWI - 8th offense.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, BAC.  Motion granted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of six (6) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision, concurrent with the sentence presently being served on case no: 08 CF 286.
The defendant has credit for 114 days.
The Court finds the defendant not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay a $2,400.00 fine plus costs ($800 X 3), total of $4,051.00;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) maintain absolute sobriety;
5) Undergo the Intoxicated Driver Assessment and Driver Safety Plan.
In addition, the Court orders a thirty-six (36) month DL revocation and Ignition Interlock period.
